8.8 Baseline governance expectations for REDCap projects
Approval of a REDCap project confirms that the project owner understands and accepts the following baseline governance expectations.
These governance rules will apply to those researchers collecting identifiable information from human participants.

8.8.1 Lawful basis and purpose limitation
You must have a clear and documented lawful basis for collecting and processing personal data (e.g. consent, public task, research in the public interest). Data collected in REDCap must only be used for the stated and approved purpose of the project and not for unrelated activities.


8.8.2 Data minimisation
Only collect the minimum personal data necessary to achieve the project objectives. Avoid collecting identifiable information unless it is strictly required.


8.8.3 Transparency and participant information
Where personal data are collected from individuals, participants must be provided with appropriate information about:

what data are being collected;
why the data are being collected;
how the data will be used;
how long the data will be retained;
who to contact regarding their data rights.



8.8.4 Access control and user management
Access to the REDCap project must be limited to authorised users only. Users must be assigned the minimum role and permissions necessary to perform their duties. Project owners are responsible for:

approving user access;
removing access when it is no longer required;
ensuring users do not share accounts or credentials.



8.8.5 Data security
REDCap must be used in accordance with institutional security guidance. Project owners must:

avoid exporting identifiable data unless necessary;
store exported data securely (think encryption);
never email unencrypted personal data;
ensure local copies of data are protected and access-controlled.



8.8.6 Confidentiality and training
All project users must understand their duty of confidentiality. Users should have completed any required institutional data protection or research ethics training relevant to the project.


8.8.7 Data quality and auditability
Project owners are responsible for ensuring data are entered accurately and responsibly. REDCap audit logs must not be disabled or circumvented. Any data corrections must follow transparent and documented procedures.


8.8.8 Data retention and deletion
Personal data must not be retained longer than necessary. Project owners must have a plan for:

data archiving;
anonymisation or pseudonymisation where appropriate;
secure deletion when the retention period ends.



8.8.9 Data subject rights
Projects must be capable of supporting data subject rights under GDPR (or the local Data Protection Legislation of their home country), including:

access to personal data;
rectification of inaccurate data;
restriction or objection where applicable;
erasure, where legally permitted.

Project owners must know how to escalate such requests through institutional channels.


8.8.10 Incident reporting
Any suspected data breach, loss, or unauthorised access must be reported immediately in accordance with institutional incident response procedures.
